<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1170,2036]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,337,1530,1556]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Discussion.</emphasis>
The Uruguayan specimens clearly belong to the taxon 
<taxonomicName authority="Sterrer &amp; Rieger, 1990" authorityName="Sterrer &amp; Rieger" authorityYear="1990" box="[990,1361,1530,1556]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="family">
Luridae 
<bibRefCitation author="Sterrer" box="[1089,1361,1530,1556]" pageId="21" pageNumber="33" refString="Sterrer, W. &amp; Rieger, M. R. (1990) New species of the statocyst-bearing marine dalyellioid genus Lurus Marcus (Luridae nov. fam., Turbellaria-Rhabdocoela). Cahiers de Biologie marine, 31, 485 - 500." type="journal article" year="1990">
Sterrer &amp; Rieger, 
<number box="[1299,1361,1530,1556]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Typical of this taxon is the fact that the overall organisation resembles that of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1067,1225,1570,1596]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Provorticidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="family">Provorticidae</taxonomicName>
and that a polylithophoric statocyst is present (
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus" box="[507,666,1610,1636]" pageId="21" pageNumber="32" refString="Marcus, E. (1950) Turbellaria Brasileiros (8). Boletins da Faculdade de Filosofia, Ciencias e Letras Universidade de Sao Paulo, Zoologia, 15, 5 - 191." type="journal article" year="1950">
Marcus 
<number box="[604,666,1610,1636]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1950.0">1950</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Faubel" box="[678,893,1610,1636]" pageId="21" pageNumber="31" refString="Faubel, A., Rohde, K. &amp; Watson, N. A. (1994) Sandy Beach Meiofauna of Eastern Australia (Southern Queensland and New South Wales). II. Luriculus australiensis, gen. et sp. nov. (Luridae: Dalyeliida: Platyhelminthes). Invertebrate Taxonomy, 8, 1009 - 1015." type="journal article" year="1994">
Faubel 
<emphasis box="[765,824,1611,1636]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[831,893,1610,1636]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sterrer" box="[905,1169,1610,1636]" pageId="21" pageNumber="33" refString="Sterrer, W. &amp; Rieger, M. R. (1990) New species of the statocyst-bearing marine dalyellioid genus Lurus Marcus (Luridae nov. fam., Turbellaria-Rhabdocoela). Cahiers de Biologie marine, 31, 485 - 500." type="journal article" year="1990">
Sterrer &amp; Rieger 
<number box="[1107,1169,1610,1636]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sterrer" box="[1181,1331,1610,1636]" pageId="21" pageNumber="33" refString="Sterrer, W. (1992) Lurus minos, the first species of Luridae (Turbellaria: Rhabdocoela) from the old world. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 105, 636 - 639." type="journal article" year="1992">
Sterrer 
<number box="[1268,1331,1610,1636]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1170,2036]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Based on the morphology of the stylet (a spirally-winding tube, two turns), the Uruguayan specimens can be classified in 
<taxonomicName authority="Marcus, 1950" authorityName="Marcus" authorityYear="1950" box="[336,681,1690,1716]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Lurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="evelinae">
<emphasis box="[336,510,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Lurus evelinae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus" box="[518,681,1690,1716]" pageId="21" pageNumber="32" refString="Marcus, E. (1950) Turbellaria Brasileiros (8). Boletins da Faculdade de Filosofia, Ciencias e Letras Universidade de Sao Paulo, Zoologia, 15, 5 - 191." type="journal article" year="1950">
Marcus, 
<number box="[622,681,1690,1716]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1950.0">1950</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus" box="[744,903,1690,1716]" pageId="21" pageNumber="32" refString="Marcus, E. (1950) Turbellaria Brasileiros (8). Boletins da Faculdade de Filosofia, Ciencias e Letras Universidade de Sao Paulo, Zoologia, 15, 5 - 191." type="journal article" year="1950">
Marcus 
<number box="[840,903,1690,1716]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1950.0">1950</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The specimens measure 0.3 mm. The stylet has an axial length of 
<number box="[411,455,1730,1756]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="165.0">165</number>
μm. Since no whole mounts are available in the material from 
<collectingCountry box="[1200,1275,1730,1756]" name="Brazil" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, the length of the stylet is estimated based on the figure drawn by 
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus" box="[759,936,1770,1796]" pageId="21" pageNumber="32" refString="Marcus, E. (1950) Turbellaria Brasileiros (8). Boletins da Faculdade de Filosofia, Ciencias e Letras Universidade de Sao Paulo, Zoologia, 15, 5 - 191." type="journal article" year="1950">
Marcus (
<number box="[863,927,1770,1796]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1950.0">1950</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Axially they measure 
<number box="[1205,1249,1770,1796]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="140.0">140</number>
μm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1170,2036]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1436,152,458]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Sterrer" box="[315,593,1810,1836]" pageId="21" pageNumber="33" refString="Sterrer, W. &amp; Rieger, M. R. (1990) New species of the statocyst-bearing marine dalyellioid genus Lurus Marcus (Luridae nov. fam., Turbellaria-Rhabdocoela). Cahiers de Biologie marine, 31, 485 - 500." type="journal article" year="1990">
Sterrer &amp; Rieger (
<number box="[524,585,1810,1836]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1990.0">1990</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
already mentioned some clear differences between 
<taxonomicName authority="Marcus, 1950" authorityName="Marcus" authorityYear="1950" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Lurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="evelinae">
<emphasis box="[1197,1370,1811,1836]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Lurus evelinae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus" pageId="21" pageNumber="32" refString="Marcus, E. (1950) Turbellaria Brasileiros (8). Boletins da Faculdade de Filosofia, Ciencias e Letras Universidade de Sao Paulo, Zoologia, 15, 5 - 191." type="journal article" year="1950">
Marcus, 
<number box="[207,266,1850,1876]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1950.0">1950</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and all other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[566,660,1850,1876]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="family">Luridae</taxonomicName>
, it was 
<bibRefCitation box="[756,994,1850,1876]" pageId="21" pageNumber="31" refString="Faubel, A., Rohde, K. &amp; Watson, N. A. (1994) Sandy Beach Meiofauna of Eastern Australia (Southern Queensland and New South Wales). II. Luriculus australiensis, gen. et sp. nov. (Luridae: Dalyeliida: Platyhelminthes). Invertebrate Taxonomy, 8, 1009 - 1015." type="journal article">
Faubel 
<emphasis box="[845,906,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[925,986,1850,1876]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1994.0">1994</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
who divided the monogeneric taxon 
<taxonomicName box="[151,242,1890,1916]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="family">Luridae</taxonomicName>
into 
<taxonomicName authority="Marcus, 1950" authorityName="Marcus" authorityYear="1950" box="[302,539,1890,1916]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Lurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[302,370,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Lurus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus" box="[377,539,1890,1916]" pageId="21" pageNumber="32" refString="Marcus, E. (1950) Turbellaria Brasileiros (8). Boletins da Faculdade de Filosofia, Ciencias e Letras Universidade de Sao Paulo, Zoologia, 15, 5 - 191." type="journal article" year="1950">
Marcus, 
<number box="[480,539,1890,1916]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1950.0">1950</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(one species: 
<taxonomicName box="[705,834,1891,1916]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Lurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="evelinae">
<emphasis box="[705,834,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. evelinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Faubel et al., 1994" authorityName="Faubel et al." authorityYear="1994" box="[900,1240,1890,1916]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Luriculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[900,1012,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Luriculus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Faubel" box="[1020,1240,1890,1916]" pageId="21" pageNumber="31" refString="Faubel, A., Rohde, K. &amp; Watson, N. A. (1994) Sandy Beach Meiofauna of Eastern Australia (Southern Queensland and New South Wales). II. Luriculus australiensis, gen. et sp. nov. (Luridae: Dalyeliida: Platyhelminthes). Invertebrate Taxonomy, 8, 1009 - 1015." type="journal article" year="1994">
Faubel 
<emphasis box="[1107,1166,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[1181,1240,1890,1916]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(four species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Faubel et al., 1994" authorityName="Faubel et al." authorityYear="1994" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Luriculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="australiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. australiensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Faubel" box="[310,537,1930,1956]" pageId="21" pageNumber="31" refString="Faubel, A., Rohde, K. &amp; Watson, N. A. (1994) Sandy Beach Meiofauna of Eastern Australia (Southern Queensland and New South Wales). II. Luriculus australiensis, gen. et sp. nov. (Luridae: Dalyeliida: Platyhelminthes). Invertebrate Taxonomy, 8, 1009 - 1015." type="journal article" year="1994">
Faubel 
<emphasis box="[399,459,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[476,537,1930,1956]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Sterrer &amp; Rieger, 1990" authorityName="Sterrer &amp; Rieger" authorityYear="1990" box="[551,942,1930,1956]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Luriculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="castor">
<emphasis box="[551,657,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. castor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sterrer" box="[666,942,1930,1956]" pageId="21" pageNumber="33" refString="Sterrer, W. &amp; Rieger, M. R. (1990) New species of the statocyst-bearing marine dalyellioid genus Lurus Marcus (Luridae nov. fam., Turbellaria-Rhabdocoela). Cahiers de Biologie marine, 31, 485 - 500." type="journal article" year="1990">
Sterrer &amp; Rieger, 
<number box="[880,942,1930,1956]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Sterrer, 1992" authorityName="Sterrer" authorityYear="1992" box="[955,1223,1930,1956]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Luriculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="minos">
<emphasis box="[955,1058,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. minos</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sterrer" box="[1067,1223,1930,1956]" pageId="21" pageNumber="33" refString="Sterrer, W. (1992) Lurus minos, the first species of Luridae (Turbellaria: Rhabdocoela) from the old world. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 105, 636 - 639." type="journal article" year="1992">
Sterrer, 
<number box="[1162,1223,1930,1956]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Sterrer &amp; Rieger, 1990" authorityName="Sterrer &amp; Rieger" authorityYear="1990" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Luriculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="tyndareus">
<emphasis box="[1289,1435,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. tyndareus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sterrer" box="[151,421,1970,1996]" pageId="21" pageNumber="33" refString="Sterrer, W. &amp; Rieger, M. R. (1990) New species of the statocyst-bearing marine dalyellioid genus Lurus Marcus (Luridae nov. fam., Turbellaria-Rhabdocoela). Cahiers de Biologie marine, 31, 485 - 500." type="journal article" year="1990">
Sterrer &amp; Rieger, 
<number box="[358,421,1970,1996]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[441,614,1971,1996]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Lurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="evelinae">
<emphasis box="[441,614,1971,1996]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Lurus evelinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
stands unique because it has paired (sometimes coalescing) testes and vasa deferentia, separate ovaries and vitellaria, and a clear differentiation between the seminal vesicle and the prostate vesicle. All other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[582,673,152,178]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="family">Luridae</taxonomicName>
have a single testis, one median vas deferens, ovovitellaria and a combined seminal vesicle and prostate vesicle. Therefore they were transferred to the new genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1324,1436,192,217]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Luriculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1324,1436,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Luriculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Faubel" box="[207,429,232,258]" pageId="22" pageNumber="31" refString="Faubel, A., Rohde, K. &amp; Watson, N. A. (1994) Sandy Beach Meiofauna of Eastern Australia (Southern Queensland and New South Wales). II. Luriculus australiensis, gen. et sp. nov. (Luridae: Dalyeliida: Platyhelminthes). Invertebrate Taxonomy, 8, 1009 - 1015." type="journal article" year="1994">
Faubel 
<emphasis box="[297,358,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[367,429,232,258]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus" box="[443,603,232,258]" pageId="22" pageNumber="32" refString="Marcus, E. (1950) Turbellaria Brasileiros (8). Boletins da Faculdade de Filosofia, Ciencias e Letras Universidade de Sao Paulo, Zoologia, 15, 5 - 191." type="journal article" year="1950">
Marcus 
<number box="[541,603,232,258]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1950.0">1950</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sterrer" box="[617,888,232,258]" pageId="22" pageNumber="33" refString="Sterrer, W. &amp; Rieger, M. R. (1990) New species of the statocyst-bearing marine dalyellioid genus Lurus Marcus (Luridae nov. fam., Turbellaria-Rhabdocoela). Cahiers de Biologie marine, 31, 485 - 500." type="journal article" year="1990">
Sterrer &amp; Rieger 
<number box="[825,888,232,258]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). One species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Sterrer &amp; Rieger, 1990" authorityName="Sterrer &amp; Rieger" authorityYear="1990" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Lurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="pollux">
<emphasis box="[1070,1222,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Lurus pollux</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sterrer" pageId="22" pageNumber="33" refString="Sterrer, W. &amp; Rieger, M. R. (1990) New species of the statocyst-bearing marine dalyellioid genus Lurus Marcus (Luridae nov. fam., Turbellaria-Rhabdocoela). Cahiers de Biologie marine, 31, 485 - 500." type="journal article" year="1990">
Sterrer &amp; Rieger, 
<number box="[151,212,272,298]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, remains a 
<emphasis box="[343,562,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">species inquirenda</emphasis>
. Although 
<taxonomicName box="[694,797,272,297]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Lurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="pollux">
<emphasis box="[694,797,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">L. pollux</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only a single testis, one medioventral vas deferens and a seminal vesicle inside the copulatory bulb, 
<bibRefCitation box="[748,986,312,338]" pageId="22" pageNumber="31" refString="Faubel, A., Rohde, K. &amp; Watson, N. A. (1994) Sandy Beach Meiofauna of Eastern Australia (Southern Queensland and New South Wales). II. Luriculus australiensis, gen. et sp. nov. (Luridae: Dalyeliida: Platyhelminthes). Invertebrate Taxonomy, 8, 1009 - 1015." type="journal article">
Faubel 
<emphasis box="[837,898,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[917,978,312,338]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1994.0">1994</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
did not place it in 
<taxonomicName box="[1221,1333,312,337]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Luriculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1221,1333,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Luriculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because vitellaria have not been observed. Besides the stylet, no other confirmative features could be observed in the live specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[363,492,392,417]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Luridae" genus="Lurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhabdocoela" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="evelinae">
<emphasis box="[363,492,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">L. evelinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[564,668,392,418]" name="Uruguay" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
. The single testis could well be two coalescing testes and no vasa deferentia were seen. However, ovaries and vitellaria seemed rather separate.
</paragraph>
